# AI-native knowledge-first (core)

> Knowledge defines, rules enforce, AI executes, humans approve.

**Human-directed agents:** When docs say people **author or update** artifacts, the intended pattern is usually a **human directing a Cursor agent** (this repo's **`.knowledge-first-system/rules/`** + **`.knowledge-first-system/skills/`**) so edits are **captured in git**, coordinated across **`knowledge/`**, product narrative under **`docs/`** (conventional layout; create when adopting), **`src/`**, and **`tests/`**, and reviewed like any other PR—humans retain **approval and accountability**; agents improve **throughput and consistency** of captured change.

**Official human docs (keep agent narrative aligned):** Index **`.knowledge-first-system/README.md`** (includes the **conventional `docs/`** layout for product artifacts). Primary entry points: **`.knowledge-first-system/executive_overview.md`** (strategy, adoption, impact) and **`.knowledge-first-system/use_guide.md`** (operations, layout, scenarios, checklists). **Knowledge model (layers, primitives, graph, validation):** **`.knowledge-first-system/specs/knowledge_model_spec.md`**. **Architecture intent documents** (conventionally **`docs/architecture/`**): **`.knowledge-first-system/specs/architecture_intent_spec.md`**. **High-level design (HLD)** (conventionally **`docs/design/`**): **`.knowledge-first-system/specs/design_spec.md`**. Test, infrastructure, and CI/CD depth: **`.knowledge-first-system/specs/test_strategy_spec.md`**, **`.knowledge-first-system/specs/infrastructure_spec.md`**, **`.knowledge-first-system/specs/cicd_spec.md`**.

This project maps knowledge-first enforcement to **Cursor rules** (constraints) and **`.knowledge-first-system/skills/`** (workflows). **Project-specific adoption**, **knowledge model** narrative, and trace model are governed by **`.knowledge-first-system/specs/knowledge_model_spec.md`** plus product docs under the conventional **`docs/prd/`**, **`docs/architecture/`**, **`docs/design/`**, and **`docs/test/`** paths when your program adds them (see **`.knowledge-first-system/README.md`**). **What to write in architecture intent docs** is governed by **`.knowledge-first-system/specs/architecture_intent_spec.md`**. **What to write in HLD** is governed by **`.knowledge-first-system/specs/design_spec.md`**.

**Knowledge model (schema and graph):** **`.knowledge-first-system/specs/knowledge_model_spec.md`** — **artifact layers**, **primitive concepts** (CON / INV / DEC / CONR / FEAT), **graph node and edge types**, **validation expectations**, and **official flow** (architecture intent → Decision → HLD; Constraint / Invariant → Spec → HLD → code → tests). Use it when aligning rules, skills, or CI with the model (RULE-011).

